data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime.** There is no workaround.

In EF Core 10, the Cosmos DB provider let you opt into sync-over-async. **EF Core 11 removes that opt-in entirely.** Calling `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, or `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now **always throws**, regardless of configuration.

### What to fix

Convert every synchronous call to its async equivalent:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This means **callers** of your repository must also go async (`async`/`await` all the way up). There is no opt-in flag to restore the old sync behavior.
